product_name: ArdellNaked Lash Clusters, Over or Underlash
summary: SummaryFrom Ardell's popular Naked collection of lightweight, barely-there lashes comes this fully-customizable, 50-piece set of style Naked Clusters. Personalize every detail of this feathery mid-volume lash from placement to length for everyday looks as individual as you.
details: DetailsFeaturesPatented cluster design on an invisible ‚ÄúInvisiband‚Äù, blends seamlessly with real lashes.50 fully customizable clusters provide up to 8 applications4 lengths, 8 MM, 10 MM, 12 MM, 14 MMTailor placement of lashes and duration of wear to your needs.To wear on the lash line, use a strip lash glue. For underlash placement, pair with Seamless Bond & Seal for up to 10 days wear or Seamless Glue & Seal for gentle, 1-day hold. (all glues are sold separately)Knot-free design means no visible, tell-tale signsBenefitsPerfect for intermediate to experienced users.Wear time: choose duration from 1 day to 10 depending on the glue.Add fullness or fill in. Stack, layer, take your look from off-duty to on-the-town.Item 2627083How To UseEasy 3-Step Application:Check fit: Align band with natural lash line to check fit. Trim excess if necessary.Apply adhesive: Apply a thin line of adhesive along band. Wait 30 seconds to set.Apply lashes: Secure lash band by pressing onto lash line.To remove, gently peel off lash strip starting at outer corner. Remove used adhesive from band and place lashes back onto tray for reuse.Precautions: Use only as directed. KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN. FOR EXTERNAL USE ONLY.

reviews.headline: Too short
reviews.comments: They are good lashes, they are the longest fullest available. I wish you had longer/fuller ones or at least more options for this brand. Now that I'm thinking about it there aren't a lot of cluster options at all.

reviews.headline: Great product
reviews.comments: My teen daughter loves these. Much better quality than others we purchased on popular marketplace. Easy to apply. You must buy the glue separately. We have bought these twice.

reviews.headline: Gorgeous
reviews.comments:
The clusters blend seamlessly with your own lashes, offering a fuller look without a heavy feel. Perfect for both everyday wear and special occasions.
Highly recommended for a subtle yet striking enhancement.

reviews.headline: Look good but packaging is terrible
reviews.comments: After buying several times, I noticed the glue that attaches the lashes to the tray is way too tight. The lashes are easy to apply & look great but I switched to another brand because the lashes got so damaged just from me trying to remove them so I wasted a lot

reviews.headline: Love these!
reviews.comments: I love these. I use them ontop of my lashes and I use 4 per eye and I just use duo black eyelash glue. Once I have them in place I use a lash tool to clamp them with my natural lashes. They stay on no lifting like I get with lash strips. I wish they sold just the 10mm and 12 separately.  I don't use the 14mm at all. New user friendly.  I actually tried them because my eyelash curler cut some of my natural eyelashes.  So I had a bald spot. I do my eye makeup curl my lashes then put on a little mascara and then these lashes. No issue with losing my natural lashes. Love them.

reviews.headline: okay
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The lashes were cute, but the glue i did not like. Made it hard for me to put on. I gave up and just used another brand of lash glue. The lashes only  lasted a few hours with the glue provided.

reviews.headline: Worst clusters I've ever tried
reviews.comments: Normally i love ardell lashes so i decided to give the clusters a try. I have been doing my own lash extensions for awhile. These are the absolute worst clusters ive ever tried. I cannot even get them off the tray and they rip apart. Ive probably got about 5 full clusters out of the whole tray. Like i said ive been doing them for awhile so i know how to grab them from the tray. I hate these so much. The kiss brand is way better.

reviews.headline: Ease of use
reviews.comments: These lashes are perfect for me. I don't particularly like wearing normal full lashes (partially because they rub on my glasses). These made it easier to pick where I wanted my lashes to be and not have to cut a pair of full lashes. They blended well with my lashes and looked great!

faceoff_positive.comments: Mostly I liked the look of these lashes. There are many sets at varying lengths so you can really customize your look to enhance the natural shape of your eye. These smaller pieces also make it much easier and less intimidating to apply.The lash glue that is included says it can last for up to 3 days and is water resistant but unfortunately most of mine fell off after one shower even while trying to keep my face dry. I reapplied and slept in them with no issues. By the end of the next day however the edges started to lift and really become a nuisance.The lashes peeled off easily but the residue of the glue was a huge pain to get off. The remover solution is very runny so it suggests putting it on a cotton bud to apply however I couldn't get enough solution on the bud to get any of glue to budge. When applying to the lashes directly as you would do with the glue (they come in identical containers) the solution easily runs into your eyes and burns so badly. I ended up having to use tweezers to separate and pick out little globs of glue which was super sketchy.Last thing of note- the base of these lashes is clear but I could still see them up close when placed under the lashes. It was my first time trying this application but I don't think it could be avoided. I will probably only try over the lashes when using these in the future.Overall I think this style of lash clusters is a great idea. I will definitely use them again but you can definitely find a cheaper pack of small cluster lashes and skip using this glue because it doesn't last that long and is a hassle to remove.
faceoff_positive.headline: Love

faceoff_negative.comments: I'll start off by saying that I have decent experience with DIY lash extensions. Many of these clusters fell apart just from pulling them out of the tray. Shortest 8mm ones completely disintegrated and were unusable. You get a lot of clusters for the money in this pack, but the quality is so poor. Out of all Ardell lash clusters, I would most recommend Seamless Wispies underlash extensions, which are the bomb, natural-looking, so affordable and easy to work with. Hope this helps someone.
